    <name>Assignment #1: Help Learners Set Goals</name>
    <intro>&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span size="3"&gt;&lt;span face="Calibri"&gt;Read &lt;span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;a title="PDF - opens in new window - Adult Learner Goals Toolkit" href="@@PLUGINFILE@@/Adult%20learner%20goals%20toolkit.pdf" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;span size="3" face="Verdana"&gt;The Adult Learner Goals Toolkit&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;span size="3"&gt;&lt;span face="Verdana"&gt; developed by the Colorado Department of Education (2004) or for ESL students, read the &lt;em&gt;Pearson Education Guide, &lt;a title="PDF - opens in new window - Learner Goal Setting" href="@@PLUGINFILE@@/RMagy_Monograph.pdf" target="_blank"&gt;Learner Goal Setting&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span size="3"&gt;&lt;span note="" span=""&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span&gt;Note&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;: Although the first reading, &lt;i&gt;The Adult Learner’s Goals Toolkit&lt;/i&gt;, is 54 pages long, it consists mostly of worksheets related to various goal-setting activities, so it is not a particularly dense reading selection. You will be able to skim through this document and select some strategies you would like to try with your students. The second reading, &lt;i&gt;the Pearson Education Guide on Learner Goal Setting,&lt;/i&gt; is a much shorter piece—but it is intended for use with ESL students.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Write a one- to two-page description of strategies you will use from the reading to strengthen learner goal setting in your program.   &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Click below on "Add my submission" to submit your reflection or copy and paste your reflection into the online text box.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
